  "instructions": [
    "Whisk eggs with soy sauce, oyster sauce, sugar, and a pinch of salt until well combined.",
    "Heat the vegetable oil in a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat and add minced garlic, cooking until aromatic.",
    "Stir in the Jamaican curry powder, Sichuan peppercorn powder, and chili flakes, cooking for 30 seconds to release flavors.",
    "Add diced bell pepper and onion, sautéing until just softened, about 3-4 minutes.",
    "Pour the egg mixture over the vegetables, letting it sit without stirring for 30 seconds.",
    "Gently swirl the skillet to create large soft curds, cooking until the eggs are set but still moist.",
    "Fold in sliced scallions and remove from heat.",
    "Serve immediately, optionally with steamed rice."
